The article discusses the ongoing political campaign by Chairman Cummings and Democrats on the House Oversight Committee to harass President Trump and his close advisors. They are specifically targeting Kellyanne Conway with allegations about the Hatch Act. The article argues that, based on long-standing precedent and constitutional protection, a President's senior advisers cannot be compelled to appear before Congress. The Department of Justice Office of Legal Counsel and White House Counsel have reaffirmed this immunity for Conway. The article includes links to the letter from the White House Counsel to Chairman Cummings and the DOJ Office of Legal Counsel opinion.